title: Intercity from Holyhead to London climbs the ramp on Anglesey
Beautiful looking Alfa 156
description:
Andy Robinson in his Alfa Romeo 156 runs down the Start/Finish straight during Qualifying for the BRSCC Alfa Romeo Championship.

Photograph taken during the Alfa Romeo Championship Qualifying session for the BRSCC Summer Solstice Raceday at Oulton Park on 25th June 2016.

title: Just edging over the rumble strip
description:
Paul McGuire from Salisbury runs his nearside wheels over the rumble strip as he accelerates away from the corner.

It seemed to me that the MX-5 class races are so competitive that if the tyres are not squealing and you aren't running over the rumble strips, you are not trying hard enough!

Photograph taken during the Mazda MX-5 Championship Qualifying session for the BRSCC Summer Solstice Raceday at Oulton Park on 25th June 2016.

title: Ferrari 328 GTB exits Old Hall corner
description: 3.2 litre Ferrari 328 GTB driven by Gary Culver exits Old Hall corner during the Pirelli Ferrari Formula Classic race at Oulton Park during the BRSCC Dubworth and FunCup racing at Oulton Park.

title: Ferrari 308 GT4 exits Old Hall corner
description: 2.9 litre Ferrari 308 GT4 driven by Terry Simpson exits Old Hall corner during the Pirelli Ferrari Formula Classic race at Oulton Park during the BRSCC Dubworth and FunCup racing at Oulton Park.

title: Gently over the crest until full grip is restored.
description:
Clive Chisnell comes over the tricky brow as he exits Old Hall Corner under gentle accelerarion.

This is a tricky corner because just when you get to where you would normally accelerate, the car is going light over the brow and so there is less grip available.  Too much power at this point can help you meet with the Marshalls in the gravel trap.

Photograph taken during the Mazda MX-5 Championship Free Practice session for the BRSCC Summer Solstice Raceday at Oulton Park on 25th June 2016.

title: Robert Oldman in his Ford Fiesta ST in the 'Pocket Rocket' Class
description:
Photograph taken during the Tunerfest North at Oulton Park on 22nd July 2017.

TimeAttack's 2017 Championship for Round 5 (of 8) is where some of the fastest and uniquely tuned cars tackle Oulton Park's 2.26 mile 'Island' Cicuit against the clock.  Some of these cars are out and out racers, not restricted by Class Rules so almost anything goes but they are sub-divided into classes according to the level of tuning that is allowed.

title: Mark Walker with his 4,228cc GN Thunderbug
description:
Mark Walker with his 1922/08 V-twin 4,228cc GN Thunderbug 'special' exits Old Hall corner and accelerates along the Avenue.  

Yes!  Two cylinders of over 2 litres each and no silencers!    Almighty noisy exhaust.  The owner was obviously not into polishing this car, purely for performance/racing.  The handling and steering must have been  .... 'interesting' .... with those skinny tyres.

Photograph taken during the Vintage Festival at Oulton Park on 10th June 2017.

title: Paris Metro #6
description:
Accelerating train in the Concorde Metro station, line 1 platform,  Paris, France.  This train is one of the newer types in use in Paris.

I deliberately blurred this photo in an effort to capture the ordered chaos of the rapid movement of a large number of people through a small area (this is a particularly narrow platform).

One of a series of photos taken during a single afternoon in the Paris metro system.
